"Income-focused investment strategies" refers to investment strategies whose primary investment objective is to generate regular income, such as dividend-paying stocks or bonds, rather than focusing solely on growth or capital preservation;
"Investment strategies" are pre-defined plans or approaches used to manage investments, such as stocks, bonds, or other assets;
"Income" in the context of investment objectives typically refers to the generation of regular, predictable returns, such as interest or dividend payments.
